ACTRESS and TV presenter Lorna Maseko was allegedly forced to cancel the launch party for her TV show, The Hostess with Lorna Maseko, because of financial problems.Lorna allegedly cancelled the show&rsquo;s season two launch party due to claims of the SABC failing to pay on time.A source close to the situation told Sunday Sun that Lorna had already sent invites and posted on her page, only to be disappointed at the last minute.&ldquo;She was looking forward to hosting and promoting her show during the launch,&rdquo; said the source.Another source claimed: &ldquo;She was crushed but what can she do, it&rsquo;s the SABC&rsquo;s fault.&rdquo;A third source said Lorna wanted to throw the party on the day her show was scheduled to be aired on TV.&ldquo;But she couldn&rsquo;t,&rdquo; said the source.SABC spokesperson Kaizer Kganyago said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re not responsible for the preparation and cancellation of her launch party.&rdquo;Lorna could not be reached for comment.